http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetris

Traditional Tetris circa 1980s

scoring based solely on clearing lines, more points the more lines simultaneously cleared

pieces have a few milliseconds on landing to rotate

7 traditional pieces

game ends when your pile hits top of screen, there is no win condition, only a lose
  - when a block gets place in either the 21st or 22nd rows then the game is over

screen is 22 high by 10 wide blocks
  - top 2 rows are not rendered
